data.value: Clearing Android accounts would remove accounts that some apps can use to automatically login. Google account clearing requires Android 8+, and non-Google account clearing requires Android 9+. This setting only applies to Launcher method of Android shared device, since the Native method always clears every account.

data.name: ClearDevicePasscodeDevicePageHelpInfo
data.value: Enable or disable the Secure Startup option, which requires an initial PIN entry to boot up the device. If Secure Startup is already disabled, the device must be factory reset to enable it. This feature applies only to Android devices that do not have file-based encryption.

data.name: ClearDevicePasscodeSharedSettingsHelpInfo
data.value: Enable or disable Android Secure Startup, which requires an initial PIN entry to boot up the device. If disabled, users cannot enable Secure Startup during passcode setup. If Secure Startup is already disabled on the device, the device must be factory reset to enable it. This feature applies only to Android devices that do not have file-based encryption.
